      "rationale": "No formal use-error review or independent analyst check was conducted. Turbulence model and hemolysis model constants were selected by a single analyst without documented justification against published guidelines. Epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal model-form uncertainty analysis comparing at least two hemolysis model formulations (e.g., Giersiepen-Wurzinger vs. Bludszuweit) with sensitivity on exponents.",
      "rationale": "Only the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model was used. No alternative model form was evaluated and no sensitivity study on model exponents was performed. Model-form uncertainty is unquantified. Critical epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Monte Carlo or equivalent UQ propagating uncertainty in all hemolysis model inputs (blood viscosity, RBC fragility constants, inlet velocity profile) to output NIH distribution.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed on geometric tolerances and rotational speed only. Blood rheology parameters and hemolysis model constants were held fixed at nominal values. Input uncertainty coverage is insufficient for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample size sufficient for statistical characterization of hemolysis variability; inter-sample variability reported.",
      "rationale": "Validation dataset consists of n=3 experimental runs at each operating point. Statistical power analysis was not performed and inter-sample variability is not reported separately from measurement uncertainty. Epistemic gap."
